CS 4307: Database Systems
=========================

Spring 2023 Syllabus
--------------------

An introduction to database systems. Topics include the design and
implementation of relational databases (B-trees, indexing, query
planning and execution, transactions, ACID semantics) as well as
data modeling and querying for applications using databases


### Prerequisites

CS 2420 and CS 2810, each with a C or better


